Defendant Gregory D Haapakoski in court with attorney Amy C Scholz.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1 of the amended information, Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT;
  -  18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  6 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Anger Mangement Counseling;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No violent contact with:  victim listed in criminal complaint.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Anger Management Counseling.
*Perform 50 hours Community Service.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be refunded to the poster);

CONDITION TIME: 90 DAYS non working hours.    Defendant to report to the Huber Facility by Friday, March 18, 2016 at 6:00 p.m.

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

EXPUNGEMENT: Request for expungement is denied by the Court.
